# Error handling

Authoritative detail: [`adr/ADR-005-error-handling-conventions.md`](adr/ADR-005-error-handling-conventions.md).

## Validation-first

- Block invalid requests **before** they become errors: UI validates input; services validate with Zod at their boundary; handlers reject malformed requests early.

## Service layer (`$lib/server/`)

- Return **`Promise<Result<T>>`** — **do not throw**. Catch external failures, map to `{ ok: false, error: AppError }`.
- Call sites: **`if (result.ok)`** before using `result.data`.

## UI and routes

- **`{#await}` `:catch`:** render **inline** error UI in the same component subtree — **no toasts, snackbars, global alerts, or cross-component error stores** for request failures.
- Errors are **local** to the component that made the request; one component’s failure must not break the rest of the page.
- **`+error.svelte`:** only for **page-level** failures (404, unrecoverable load, unhandled load throw) — not for routine API/component failures when the shell still renders.

## Chat exception (single layout escape)

- **Persistent chat unavailable** (health/upstream/config): may surface **once** at **layout**, mark chat unavailable, keep slash commands / nav — no `+error.svelte`, no blocking content routes. **Single message failures** stay **inline** in chat.

## Upstream / Anthropic

- Map to generic user messaging — **do not** forward provider error bodies or stacks to the client (see ADR-005 Rule 8).

## `hooks.server.ts`

- **`handleError`:** log full detail **server-side**; return **sanitised** `message` / `code` to the client — no stack, paths, or secrets.

## Escalation

- Only when no local handler can communicate to the user; document in a **comment** at the escalation point — no silent rethrow.
